- The top-level try/catch in withValidatedCoords stays as a belt-and-suspenders safety net.","steps":[{"id":"step_0","description":"Update `fetchWeather` to return `{ ok: true, data: { latitude, longitude, timezone, current, hourly } }` on success and `{ ok: false, error: { code: 'WEATHER_API_ERROR', message } }` on failure. Wrap the entire body in a try/catch to also capture unexpected errors (network failures, JSON parse errors). (req 1)","status":"done"},{"id":"step_1","description":"Update `analyzeDirections` to check `.ok` on each fetchWeather result from Promise.all. If any failed, return `{ ok: false, error: { code: 'DIRECTION_ANALYSIS_ERROR', message } }`. On success, unwrap `.data` from each result for scoring. Return `{ ok: true, data: { origin, directions } }`. (req 2)","status":"done"},{"id":"step_2","description":"Update `getWeather` handler callback to check the Result from fetchWeather: return `c.json(result.data)` on ok, or `c.json({ error: true, message: result.error.message }, 500)` on failure. (req 3)","status":"done"},{"id":"step_3","description":"Update `getDirections` handler callback to check the Result from analyzeDirections: same ok/error mapping as getWeather. (req 3)","status":"done"},{"id":"step_4","description":"Update `withValidatedCoords` — add a comment clarifying the try/catch is a safety net for unexpected runtime errors, not for expected function failures which now use Result. (req 4)","status":"done"},{"id":"step_5","description":"Update `testFetchWeatherStructure` to unwrap `.data` from the Result. Add a new test `testFetchWeatherResultError` that verifies a bad-status API response returns `{ ok: false }` (via an impossible lat). Update handler-level tests if their assertions need adjusting. Run all tests. (req 5)","status":"done"}]},"planMessageIds":[1781874013239514],"approvalMessageId":1781874629840624,"workMessageIds":[1781874679326474,1781874721592387,1781874753908175,1781874754781124,1781874763714789,1781874799872287,178187